# Judge-Ready Documentation

Write for smart readers who may not be engineers. Use plain language first, then technical detail. Prefer diagrams and tables when they make the system easier to explain out loud.

Every major document should answer:

- What problem are we solving?
- How does the system work?
- What evidence shows this can become production-grade?
